Ruby naming conventions:
------------------------

   local variables,
   arrays,
   hashes,
   method names
      begin with lower case letter

   global variables
      begin with $

   instance variables
      begin with @
      (@ represents 'attribute of an object')

   class variables
      begin with @@
      (@@ represents 'attribute for all related objects')

   constants,
   class names,
      begin with capital letter e.g.
      class Myclass
         def etc...

      create an instance:
      myinstance = Myclass.new(&quot;myparam&quot;)

   symbols
      begin with :
      :varname - pass in a symbol i.e. name of variable not value</pre></div><div class="clear"></div><div class="footer">Powered by <a href="http://www.sinatrarb.com/">Sinatra</a>,
